  <div id="tabs-1" style="overflow-y:auto">The IEEE Industry Applications Society (IAS) is one of the world’s largest organizations specializing in global design, development, application, and management of electrical and electronic systems, apparatus, devices and controls. <br><br>
The scope of the Industry Applications Society, as a transnational organization, is the advancement of the theory and practice of electrical and electronic engineering in the development, design, manufacture and application of electrical systems, apparatus, devices and controls to the processes and equipment of industry and commerce; the promotion of safe, reliable and economic installations; industry leadership in energy conservation and environmental, health, and safety issues; the creation of voluntary engineering standards and recommended practices; and the professional development of its membership. <br><br>

The IAS has one of the largest special interest programs of any IEEE society, which include:
      <br><br>
IEEE IAS Annual Meeting<br>
Energy Conversion Congress and Exposition<br>
Applied Power Electronics Conference<br>
Cement Industry Conference<br>
Industrial Energy Efficiency Workshop<br>
and Commercial Power Systems Conference<br>
Petroleum and Chemical Industry Conference<br>
Pulp and Paper Industry Conference<br>
Rural Electric Power Industry Conference<br>
      <br><br>
      <b>Mission:</b>

<br><br>
IEEE IAS strives to promote the advancement of the theory and practice of electrical and electronic engineering in the development, design, manufacture and application of electrical systems, apparatus, devices and controls to the processes and equipment of industry and commerce; the promotion of safe, reliable and economical installations; industry leadership in energy conservation and environmental health and safety issues; the creation of voluntary engineering standards and recommended practices; and the professional development of its membership. 
<br><br>
      
      <b>Vision:</b>

<br><br>
IAS holds its vision to be a world leader in the advancement of technology and dissemination of technical information to support professionals engaged in the applications of electrical and electronic engineering to industry.</div>
	<div id="tabs-2">IAS (Industry Applications Society) is one of the chapter under IEEE-TSEC. It is the oldest and the most documented society. It is dedicated in providing up to data information in the fields of robotics in addition to electronics and enhance their application. It provides its student members with various workshops, seminars, conferences so as to make them familiar with the latest technological development. 
<br><br>
IEEE-TSEC IAS holds an Industrial Forum, during the entire year. IEEE-TSEC IAS also has a Distinguished Lecturer program, where a noted dignitary from IEEE comes to our college to present a seminar or a conference on current technical innovations. 
<br><br>
<b>INDUSTRIAL FORUM</b>
<br><br>

IEEE-TSEC IAS organizes Industrial Forum. In the Industrial Forum we place the members with a particular firm and the members work on a project given by that particular firm and in return receive a Letter of Appreciation, as well as a certificate of excellence from the society. 
<br><br>
Industrial Forum is organized every year in the even semester. It gives the members an opportunity to work, in an industrial environment, gain knowledge and experience
<br><br>
      <b>Industrial Forum 2013</b>
<br><br>
In February, 2013 IEEE- TSEC IAS members visited Excelsior Embedded Solutions. It’s a company aiming at making robotics and embedded systems a household term in INDIA. Another company named Provotech which is primarily a Research and Development based company in field of Robotics and Embedded System Design. 
<br><br>
Excelsior Embedded Solutions and Provotech supported us by giving our students an opportunity to do internship under their guidance. Students were selected on the basis of their interviews. 
<br><br>
      <b>THE 2ND INDIAN IAS STUDENT BRANCH CHAPTER WORKSHOP</b>
<br><br>

2nd Indian IAS Student Branch Chapter Workshop was organized by IEEE-TSEC IAS on April 6, 2013 and April 7, 2013. The workshop was held in Thadomal Shahani Engineering College, Bandra (W). The workshop was organized to discuss informative and knowledge based topics. The workshop had participants coming from various student branches all over India. The total attendance for the workshop was 60. The delegates present at the workshop were:
      <br><br>
      <ul>
        <li> Mr. Blake Lloyd –President, IEEE.</li> 
        <li> Mr. Peter Magyar – IAS CMD Chair.</li>
        <li> Mr. Shrikanth Vasudevan Pillai – IAS SB Chapters Chair, R10, IAS CMD, SB Chapter development Committee Chair.</li>
        <li> Mr. Narayanan A.M –Head, Energy Efficiency Division Energy Management Center, Dept of power, Govt of Kerala, India.</li>
        <li> Dr. Mrs. Geetanjali Vaidya-Pune Section IEEE PES/IAS Chapter Advisor.</li>
        <li> Mr. A. M Narayanan –Head, Energy Efficiency Division made people understand how energy efficiency is taken into considerations in power system</li></ul>
<br><br>
Electric Car or Renewable energy sources – a hype or solution was presented by Mr. Peter Magyar
<br><br>
IEEE-TSEC Industry Applications Society holds two festivals during the course of one academic year: TECHTRIX, during the even semester, and FUSION during the odd semester.</div>
  <div id="tabs-3"><b>Techtrix</b>
    <br><br>
TECHTRIX is an intra- collegiate even semester festival conducted by the IEEE IAS student chapter branch of Thadomal Shahani. Usually held during the month of February, it is among the first few events of the new academic semester, hence invites a huge amount of crowd. Students participate in huge numbers in the various workshops and seminars conducted by renowned professionals in the field of electronics.
<br><br>
<b>TECHTRIX 2015</b>
    <br><br>
Techtrix 2015 was held on February 14, 2015. IAS this year hosted a workshop titled, MOBILE PHONE TEARDOWN conducted by EDUCATION DEBUNKED. The distinguished speakers for the day were Mr. Deepak Gupta and Ms. Anisha Pillay. The workshop was of reverse engineering of a mobile phone. 
<br><br>
    <b>TECHTRIX 2014</b>
    <br><br>
Techtrix 2014 was held on February 14, 2014. It included of a robotic workshop named Armbotics. The workshop Armbotics was conducted by IEEE-TSEC CONATUS, the technical team of IEEE- TSEC.
In the workshop the participants made a level 1 bot and made a robotic arm. The arm is remote controlled and is capable to lift and place objects.
<br><br>
    <b>TECHTRIX 2013</b>
    <br><br>
The festival was held on March 11, 2013 and March12, 2013. It included of a two day workshop named Cran-o-bot a level 1 robotics workshop. On day one of the workshop the participants made a level 1 bot. On day two the participants were taught to make the robotic arm. The arm is capable to lift and place objects. The workshop helped the participants gain a good knowledge of robotics. The event received huge response and was successful due to the positive feedback.
    <br><br>
    <b>Blitz</b>
    <br><br>
BLITZ or FUSION as it was earlier called is a two day festival conducted during the even semester. Blitz on day 1 often holds workshops which are advancements of the knowledge imbibed during the seminars and workshops conducted during techtrix. These workshops thus enhance the application skills of the attendees. The second day comprises of THE DISTINGUISHED LECTURER PROGRAM. These DLPs have dignitaries conducting seminars on various topics of their research. They are designed to motivate and inspire students.
<br><br>
    <b>BLITZ 2014</b>
    <br><br>
It was held on 21st and 22nd August.
Blitz 2014 was a 2 day affair, with the first day having a level one robotic workshop, conducted by the technical team of IEEE-TSEC, Conatus. It was the advanced level of the workshop that was held in February. The participants were taught to make a Robotic Arm and its applications. It had a participation of 50 students.<br>
The second day of Blitz 2014 had a Distinguished Lecturer Program. It was graced by the dignitary Prof Dr. S.S.Murthy. Dr. S.S.Murthy spoke on the topic, Renewable Energy Systems for Grid fed and off grid power generation. 
The D.L.P was followed by a motivational seminar by Dr.Jonathan Joshi on college start-ups. He encouraged the students to chase their dream and think out of the box. Also, he informed the students the entire process to start a company. Thus, during the feedback session, many participants vowed to take the tough path and work towards their dream to own a company.<br>
This event received an overwhelming response with over 100 participants.</div>
